<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Speaker Calls for Diplomatic Solution to Crimean Problem </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Speaker Calls for Diplomatic Solution to Crimean Problem </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106153394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1405 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0106153394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and Mikhail </F>
Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev June 1 TASS -- "The wrong regional policy of 
the former Soviet Union and the uncertainty of the fate of the 
Black Sea Fleet are the top two objective causes of the Crimean 
problem," Ukrainian parliament chairman Oleksandr Moroz said. 
  Speaking at a session of the parliament on Wednesday, Moroz 
said that among the subjective causes are "intolerance in 
solving ethnic problems and the clash of several nationalist 
tendencies." 
  "It is necessary now to neutralise these factors as soon as 
possible by restoring economic ties and providing conditions for 
normal rest and recreation in the Crimea," Moroz said. 
  He stressed that Ukraine must use all possible diplomatic 
channels to ease tension and put the problem within the 
constitutional framework, without using force. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

