<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   General Orders Cossacks `To Be Ready To Defend' State </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    General Orders Cossacks `To Be Ready To Defend' State </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0106114494 Kiev MOLOD UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 31 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU0106114494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev MOLOD UKRAYINY </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Volodymyr Prytula, MOLOD UKRAYINY special </F>
correspondent: "Cossacks Have Arrived!"] 
  [Text] Last Saturday [28 May], the so-called "Great 
Cossack Assembly" with the participation of leaders of the 
Ukrainian and Russian cossackdom was to be held in Simferopol. 
However, in all likelihood, the organizers of the action had a 
purely political goal -- to help local separatists. That is why 
nothing came out of the "Great Assembly." Representatives of 
the majority of Russia's cossack regions did not arrive at the 
assembly. Ukrainian cossacks stated their protest to organizers 
of the provocation. Hetman [cossack leader] of the Ukrainian 
Zaporizhzhya cossackdom General V. Mulyava qualified the holding 
of the "assembly" as interference into the internal affairs of 
our state. Regional organizations of the Ukrainian cossackdom 
received a telegram signed by Hetman Mulyava ordering them to be 
ready to defend Ukraine's territorial integrity. The 
make-believe cossack conference concluded with the report from 
Simferopol's Kievskiy Rayon Department of Internal Affairs: In 
the "Moskva" hotel, a group of "cossacks" raped a woman, who was 
also staying at that hotel.... 

</TEXT>

