<F P=106> [Leonid Pozdeyev report: "Urals `Blue Helmets' Bring Peace"] </F>
  [Text] Colonel General Yuriy Grekov, commander of the 
Urals Military District troops, has conducted an inspection of 
the Russian battalion of peacekeeping forces formed on the basis 
of the Urals Military District. 
  The battalion is staffed exclusively by volunteers. 
Lieutenant Colonel Aleksandr Terekhin is commander of the Urals 
"blue helmets." Under an interstate agreement reached under the 
aegis of the United Nations, the Urals battalion, together with 
other Russian peacekeeping subunits, will be located along the 
border between Georgia and Abkhazia. 

