<H3> <TI>   DPRK Delegation Hosted by Liberal Democrats </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Delegation Hosted by Liberal Democrats </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106175594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1508 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0106175594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aleksandr Vengerovskiy, deputy chairman of the 
Liberal Democratic Party of Russia [LP], on Tuesday hosted a 
delegation of North Korea's Labor Party arriving in Moscow at 
the LDP's invitation. 
  The Korean delegation pointed to the LDP leadership's active 
position on restoring and maintaining good relations between the 
two countries, an LDP spokesman said in a statement on Wednesday. 
  LDP representatives handed the visiting delegation a stellar 
of Corinthian marble to help strengthen the foundation of a 
monument to "the Chuchkhe Ideas" in Pyongyang, says the 
statement. 
  The North Korean delegation is expected to visit Vladimir, 
Kovrov, and St. Petersburg to meet members of LDP local cells, 
visit defense-related plants, and go on a sight-seeing tour of 
St. Petersburg. 

