<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Condemns State of Emergency in Dniester </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Condemns State of Emergency in Dniester </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106144394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1345 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0106144394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Demidetskiy] </F>
  [Text] Kishinev [Chisinau] June 1 TASS -- "By prolonging 
the state of emergency in the Dniester area, the Tiraspol 
leaders have grossly violated the agreement on the peaceful 
settlement of the Dniester conflict, signed by the presidents of 
Russia and Moldavia [Moldova]," co-chairman of the Joint Control 
Commission for promoting stability in the conflict area, First 
Deputy Interior Minister of Moldavia Viktor Katane said here 
today. 
  As earlier reported, president of the unrecognised Dniester 
republic Igor Smirnov has decreed to prolong the state of 
emergency on the left-hand bank of the Dniester beginning from 
June 1. The state of emergency was announced on January 18 to 
prevent the holding of pre-term elections to the Moldavian 
parliament in the Dniester area. 
  According to Katane, the state of emergency envisages the 
toughening of the border regime by the self-styled Dniester 
republic and deployment of additional paramilitary units within 
the safety zone. He described as far-fetched the arguments of 
the Tiraspol authorities that the state of emergency was 
necessary to combat crime in the region. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

