<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk: Russian Fleet Should Be Based at Russian Bases </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk: Russian Fleet Should Be Based at Russian Bases </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106142394 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 1100 GMT 1 June 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0106142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Kiev, 1 June -- Leonid Kravchuk, president of 
Ukraine made a speech on the current situation in Crimea at a 
session of the Ukrainian parliament. [passage omitted] 
  Touching on problems of the Black Sea Fleet, Leonid Kravchuk 
noted that there are two tasks which must be tackled first: To 
resolve the problem of the deployment of both fleets at various 
bases and to clearly define the status of the Russian fleet 
which is based on Ukrainian territory. The problem of the Black 
Sea Fleet should, in the president's view, meet Ukraine's 
national interests and should guarantee Russia's security on its 
foreign borders. 
  However, the president considers that in the future the 
Russian fleet should be based exclusively at bases on Russian 
territory. 
  At the end, Leonid Kravchuk stressed that the regulation of 
the "Crimean problem" is of vital importance for Ukraine, 
Crimea, Europe and the world. 
  Leonid Kravchuk answered questions from journalists. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

