<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rybkin Says CIS States May Return to Euro-Asian Union Idea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rybkin Says CIS States May Return to Euro-Asian Union Idea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206104894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1011 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 2 TASS -- "The time will come when our 
two countries will again return to the Euro-Asian union idea, 
first suggested by Kazakhstan President Nursultan Nazarbayev, 
notwithstanding the fact that some CIS members are not prepared 
so far to join such a union, State Duma Speaker Ivan Rybkin said 
here on Thursday during a meeting with Kazakhstan Foreign 
Minister Kanat Saudabayev. 
  "However, it may so happen that by that time the 
legislations 
of our states will become so different from one another that a 
good deal of effort would have to be made to bring them closer 
together again," Rybkin said. 
  In view of this, "it is essential to seek cooperation in the 
lawmaking process within the CIS framework so that the 
legislations of our states would be adequate to one another as 
much is possible", pointed out the speaker of the lower house of 
the Russian parliament. 

</TEXT>

