<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lithuania Gives Economic Statistics on Baltic Countries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lithuania Gives Economic Statistics on Baltic Countries </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206194494 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
1300 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0206194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lithuanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The statistical department attached to the 
Lithuanian Government has announced some information about the 
situation in all three Baltic countries. 
  It stated that the lowest inflation in April was in 
Lithuania 
-- 1.6 percent -- and the highest in Estonia -- 3.1 percent; 
inflation in Latvia was 2.7 percent. But throughout the whole 
of last year, from April 1993 to April 1994, the lowest 
inflation was in Latvia -- 37.4 percent -- and the highest in 
Lithuania -- 78.5 percent. 
  Fewer industrial products were sold in April than in March 
in 
all three states: in Lithuania, 17 percent less, in Latvia, 15.9 
percent less, and in Estonia -- 14.3 percent less. 
  Between April 1993 and April 1994, industrial output 
declined 
in Lithuania by 43.6 percent, and in Latvia by 18.8 percent; 
there is no information about this from Estonia, ELTA 
[Lithuanian News Agency] reports. 
  The highest unemployment in April was in Latvia -- 6.6 
percent; unemployment in Lithuania was 3.6 percent, and in 
Estonia 2.3 percent. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

