<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on ROK President Kim's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on ROK President Kim's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kim Predicts `Bright Future' </H4>

<F P=102> LD0206185294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1749 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206185294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Solntsev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 2 TASS -- Korean President Kim Yong-sam 
said on Thursday he is quite convinced that "a very bright 
future lies ahead of us" in Russo-Korean relations. 
  Speaking at a dinner hosted by President Yeltsin, Kim 
Yong-sam noted that "we will surely share a great future 
together if the advanced technology and vast natural resources 
of the Russian Federation are combined with the industrial 
development and business management expertise of Korea." 
  Kim Yong-sam expressed confidence that "great friendship and 
trust" shared by the two presidents, despite their relatively 
brief association, will "serve as a strong catalyst for further 
developing relations between our two nations." 
  The president said he hopes that "the Russian Federation 
will 
actively participate in the Asia-Pacific economic cooperation 
forum." 
  According to him, documents concerning the Korean war of 
1950- 1953 which were handed today to the Korean president by 
Boris Yeltsin "will stand as a symbol of our firm determination 
to make a fresh start in our relations, putting behind us our 
unfortunate past relations during the era of Cold War." 
  Kim Yong-sam expressed gratitude to the Government of the 
Russian Federation for "its positive participation in the 
international movement to block the development of nuclear arms 
by North Korea." 

</TEXT>

