<H3> <TI>   Further on ROK President Kim's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on ROK President Kim's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kim on Assistance to DPRK </H4>

<F P=102> LD0206125994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1158 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206125994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Aleksandr Kopnov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 2 TASS -- South Korean President Kim 
Yong-sam said his country can render economic aid to North Korea 
if the latter allows nuclear inspections on its territory. 
  Addressing Russian lawmakers on Thursday he said that, 
proceeding from the principle of national co-flourishment, South 
Korea will develop the policy of active cooperation with 
Pyongyang. Seoul is also ready to promote better relations 
between North Korea, the United States and Japan, according to 
the president. 
  Kim Yong-sam said that he had discussed with the Russian 
president bilateral relations in full volume, including the 
issue of making "North Korea refrain from developing nuclear 
weapons". 
  State Duma Chairman Ivan Rybkin said that Russia understands 
the wish of the Korean people "to reunite into a single and 
flourishing state in the Far East". Russia is ready to promote 
the reunification, he added. 

</TEXT>

