<H3> <TI>   Kim Says Yeltsin To Visit ROK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Says Yeltsin To Visit ROK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0306084394 Seoul YONHAP in English 0701 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0306084394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, June 3 (YONHAP) -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin will visit South Korea in the near future, President Kim 
Yong-sam said Friday [3 June]. 
  Kim told South Korean correspondents here that Yeltsin had 
accepted his invitation to visit Seoul and expected that it 
would take place soon. 
  Considering that Yeltsin's term of office expires in June 
1996, he is expected to visit South Korea next year, a senior 
member of Kim's entourage said. 

</TEXT>

