<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Meets State Duma Chairman Rybkin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Meets State Duma Chairman Rybkin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206213294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1321 
GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0206213294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 2 June -- The visit of the head of the 
Republic of Korea is symbolic, "because it is taking place at a 
time when our countries are in the midst of socio-economic 
transformations and the break-up of out-dated systems and 
patterns of social development," State Duma Chairman Ivan Rybkin 
said after his meeting with ROK President Kim Yong-sam at the 
President Hotel today. 
  The chairman of the State Duma hoped that multi-faceted ties 
will develop between the Republic of Korea and Russia and that 
contacts between their supreme legislative bodies--the Federal 
Assembly of Russia and the National Assembly of the Republic of 
Korea--play a proper part in this. 
  In reply Kim Yong-sam said he was delighted to meet the 
leaders of a parliament that was elected in free elections for 
the first time in Russia. 
  He expressed gratitude to the State Duma for its adoption of 
a legislative act rehabilitating repressed Koreans in Russia and 
touched on the problems of nuclear disarmament on the Korean 
peninsula and Russia's participation in the Asian-Pacific 
Economic Cooperation program. 
  The Korean president expressed the hope that his "visit will 
serve as a stimulus for shifting our bilateral relations onto a 
qualitatively new and higher level of constructive and mutually 
complementary partnership." 

</TEXT>

