<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lukin Says Russia Should Pressure DPRK on NPT Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lukin Says Russia Should Pressure DPRK on NPT Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206101994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0908 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206101994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Nikolay Geronin and Vladimir </F>
Solntsev] 
  [Text] Moscow June 2 TASS -- Russia should mount pressure 
on North Korea to observe the nuclear non-proliferation regime, 
according to Vladimir Lukin, chairman of the State Duma 
Committee on International Affairs, who, however, did not say 
directly whether sanctions should be imposed on Pyongyang. 
  "Our attitude to the problem of nuclear armaments of any 
state is resolutely negative. Surely, it is better to reach an 
agreement than impose sanctions, but the non-proliferation 
regime should be maintained very strictly", he told TASS on 
Thursday. 
  Lukin, who participated in Russian-South Korean talks on 
Thursday, said that "Russia is especially not interested in the 
appearance of new nuclear states on its borders" and added that 
it is necessary to hold a dialogue with Pyongyang when possible. 
  If the dialogue fails "then those countries which do not 
want 
to abide by international and even their own decisions should be 
convinced more resolutely", he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

