<H3> <TI>   Bosnian Serb Leader Karadzic To Visit Moscow 8-12 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bosnian Serb Leader Karadzic To Visit Moscow 8-12 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206213994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1548 
GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0206213994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Konstantin Pribytkov] </F>
  [Text] Geneva, 2 June -- Bosnian Serb leader Radovan 
Karadzic plans to visit Moscow next week. The Serbian leader, 
who is also well known as a poet, said today in an exclusive 
interview with an ITAR-TASS correspondent in Geneva that the 
trip is connected with his being awarded the literary Mikhail 
Sholokhov Prize by the Russian Union of Writers. In addition, 
Radovan Karadzic intends to make use of his stay in Moscow to 
have talks about the rapid achievement of peace in Bosnia and 
Herzegovina. 
  According to the Serbian leader, the trip is planned for 
about 8-12 June. 

</TEXT>

