<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Greek Foreign Minister's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Greek Foreign Minister's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Arrives in Murmansk </H4>

<F P=102> LD0206132194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1126 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Murmansk June 2 TASS -- Greek Foreign Minister 
Karolos Papoulias, currently paying an official visit to Russia, 
arrived in Murmansk today. He will meet Yevgeniy Komarov, head 
of the regional administration. They are expected to discuss 
the possibility of greek participation in the development of the 
economy of the Kola Peninsula. 
  The agenda of the Greek minister's brief stay here includes 
a 
sightseeing tour of Murmansk and a visit to the Annunciation 
Church in the ancient town of Kola. 
  The Greek foreign minister will return from Murmansk to 
Moscow today. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

