<F P=106> [Report by Igor Cherevko: "No Boarding Without a Visa"] </F>
  [Text] A visa requirement imposed by Lithuania to 
transit its territory by passengers from other CIS states has 
created serious problems in the relations between the October 
Railroad and the Ukrainian Administration of Railroads. 
Since this country imposed the visa regime, the St. 
Petersburg-Lvov train, which transits Lithuania, has been empty 
in both directions. 
  The Ukrainian Administration of Railroads asked the October 
Railroad to resolve with the Republic of Lithuania the question 
of repealing the transit visa requirement. There is a precedent: 
Passengers on the St. Petersburg-Kaliningrad train do not need 
such visas. The management of the Ukrainian Administration of 
Railroads suggested that the October Railroad stop selling 
tickets for this train until the problem with Lithuania is 
settled. 

</TEXT>

