<H3> <TI>   Duma Member Shot at Home, in Critical Condition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma Member Shot at Home, in Critical Condition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206125594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1101 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Moscow Duma member Nikolay Moskovchenko was 
heavily wounded at the entrance to his house Wednesday night. 
As Interfax has learned from Moscow's law enforcement bodies, 
he was struck by three bullets. No other details are known yet, 
except that Moskovchenko is in an intensive care unit in 
critical condition but is conscious. 
  The Prosecutor General's Office has initiated legal 
proceedings, and an investigation is under way. 
  The State Duma member Andrey Aizderdzis was shot dead in the 
town of Khimki near Moscow at the end of April. Police believe 
his killer was hired. 

