<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Nuclear Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Upper House Approves 55-Trillion-Ruble Defense Budget </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Upper House Approves 55-Trillion-Ruble Defense Budget </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206181094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1630 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The increase in Russia's military expenditures from 
37 to 55 trillion rubles reflects the Defense Ministry's factual 
expenses taking into account its debts accumulated over the last 
five months, deputy chairman of the parliamentary committee for 
defense, Aleksandr Piskunov said today. 
  As has already been reported, the Federation Council (the 
upper house of the Russian parliament) voted in favor of 
increasing the defense expenditures to 55 trillion rubles 
Thursday. 
  "Either we openly admit that the expenditure will be that 
high, or we will end the year with a debt of 18 trillion 
rubles," Piskunov said in an interview with Interfax. 
  Piskunov believes that the Defense Ministry should develop a 
program for the optimization of its expenses, structure and 
personnel in the near future. 

</TEXT>

