<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Nuclear Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Nuclear Submarine Begins Static Tests </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Nuclear Submarine Begins Static Tests </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0206082794 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 28 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0206082794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Vladimir Gundarov report: "Kursk Launch Ceremony"] </F>
  [Text] Static tests of the Kursk, a new nuclear missile 
submarine, began at Severodvinsk on 23 May. Captain First Class 
V. Rozhkov has been appointed its commander. 
  As Ivan Vasilyev, the senior official responsible for the 
order, has noted, the nuclear powered vessel has a number of 
improvements, including in its navigational systems package, and 
the crew's living conditions have been improved. The new 
nuclear-powered vessel will go into service with the Russian 
Navy next December. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

