<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Federation Council Holds Debate on Russian Budget </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Federation Council Holds Debate on Russian Budget </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206104394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1021 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 2 TASS -- The Council of the Federation, 
upper chamber of the Russian Parliament, voted to complete the 
discussion of the 1994 federal budget in one hour, but even two 
hours were not enough for this. Chairman of the Chamber's 
Budget Committee Nikolay Gonchar told ITAR-TASS during the break 
that the mps would spend as much time on this problem as 
necessary. "This is the main item on today's agenda," he added. 
  Gonchar explained that the deliberations were held behind 
closed doors because the chamber was discussing defence 
allocations. "The search for compromises is proceeding against 
the background of a very keen debate, because everybody is short 
of money," he stated. The mps plan to offer the state duma, 
which approved the draft budget in first reading, to discuss 
anew several items in the spendings part of the draft. 
  "Faced with the choice of whether to have good relations 
with 
the government or to uphold the interests of the state, the mps 
will definitely choose the latter," Gonchar believes. He 
stressed that "there is no factional or political struggle in 
the upper chamber, but merely a dispute over regional 
interests". "We are apparently faced with the need to 
redistribute the available means, and this is a very painful 
process," he added. Gonchar also said that his committee was 
backing the stand assumed by the chairman of the Duma Committee 
for Economic Affairs Sergey Glazyev, but several economic acts 
were needed to implement his proposals and this would take time. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

