<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Spending Increased to R55 Trillion </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Spending Increased to R55 Trillion </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206120894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1137 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206120894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 2 TASS -- The Russian Federation 
Council, which approved the key figures of the draft budget on 
Thursday, increased defence appropriations in 1994 from 
initially envisaged 37 trillion rubles to 55 trillion, according 
to First Deputy Defence Minister Andrey Kokoshin. 
  He told TASS by telephone that lawmakers adopted the 
decision 
mostly because the 37-trillion appropriations would mean a 
closure for many defence enterprises and mass unemployment. 

</TEXT>

