<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tatarstan President Praises Yeltsin's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tatarstan President Praises Yeltsin's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206115594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1112 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206115594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Lyudmila Ermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 2 TASS -- "The strengthening of mutual 
understanding between the Russian Federation and Tatarstan, upon 
which we were relying, was accomplished", according to Tatarstan 
President Mintimer Shaymiyev, now in Moscow in his position as 
delegate to the Federation Council. 
  Responding to an ITAR-TASS question about his main 
conclusions after Russian President Boris Yeltsin's visit to his 
republic, Shaymiyev said that, after the signing of the 
bilateral treaty between the center and Tatarstan, "peace and 
accord have settled in the republic. And it is very important 
that Boris Nikolayevich (Yeltsin) saw the support for that act 
on peoples' faces". 
  The creation of a bilateral commission headed by the 
Tatarstan leader and Russia's first vice-premier allows the two 
sides to monitor the fulfillment of the treaty's 12 articles, 
Shaymiyev said. He continued on to say that the document makes 
it possible to "develop a conception for the decentralization of 
the federal economy, using the example of Tatarstan, and to 
remove the petty tutelage of the centre". 
  Time has shown that "Tatarstan's economic course, which 
differs somewhat from the federal one, has justified itself", 
the republican president noted. The best indicator of that is 
that "the population has not been impoverished". 
  "The republic's position in the fight against crime has also 
been recognized", Shaymiyev said, explaining that his republic's 
law enforcement bodies are "in control of the situation and have 
overcome their fear of the underworld". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

