<F P=106> [Item from column of ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA/ITAR-TASS </F>
correspondent reports: "Conference in Khabarovsk"] 
  [Text] The role and tasks of the representatives of the 
Russian Federation president and the organs of state power in 
the realization of the Treaty on Social Accord at the level of 
federation components are being discussed at a zonal conference 
in Khabarovsk. The Russian Federation president's 
representatives in krays and oblasts of the Far East and Eastern 
Siberia have gathered here. 
  Conference participants note that the current situation 
dictates the need to amend the activity of the president's 
representatives. The functional obligations of all organs of 
power at federal and regional levels must be clearly defined so 
that they work in harmony, without obstructing one another. 

