<H3> <TI>   Transbaykal Miners Start Three-Day Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Transbaykal Miners Start Three-Day Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0206152994 Moscow TRUD in Russian 2 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0206152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow TRUD </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "Here Is the News" rubric: </F>
"Miners Striking Again"] 
  [Text] Miners in the Baykal and Transbaykal areas stopped 
mining and dispatching fuel to consumers yesterday. With the 
exception of workers at two opencut mines, the 20,000-strong 
collective of the "Vostsibugol" joint-stock company is insisting 
on immediate payment of debts which now amount to approximately 
170 billion rubles [R]. The principal debtors are power 
industry workers, specifically in Khabarovsk and Maritime Krays. 
However, the list of demands put forward by the miners is 
topped by an appeal to the Russian Federation Government, which 
they say should allocate funds to pay off debts of R69 billion 
run up by budget-financed and other organizations 
  In accordance with a statement made by Vladimir Solomin, 
chairman of the joint-stock company strike committee, the strike 
action is scheduled to last for three days and also has a 
political angle: The East Siberian miners are demanding the 
resignation of the government and early presidential elections. 

</TEXT>

