<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kebich at Top of Political Popularity Chart </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kebich at Top of Political Popularity Chart </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206180994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1630 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206180994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belarusian Prime Minister Vyacheslav Kebich's 
political popularity has doubled, officials at the Belarusian 
Political Research Center Eridan announced today. 
  Kebich leads the list of the officially registered 
candidates 
to the post of president with 372,000 signatures in support of 
his candidacy. 
  Ex-speaker of the Belarusian parliament Stanislav 
Shushkevich 
and leader of the Agrarian Party Aleksandr Dubko secured the 
smallest number of signatures (123,000 and 117,000, 
respectively). The other candidates are former head of the 
temporary parliamentary commission for combating corruption 
Aleksandr Lukashenko, Secretary of the Communist Party's Central 
Committee Vassiliy Novikov and leader of the Popular Front Zenon 
Poznyak. 
  An opinion poll held by the Eridan Center revealed that the 
popularity of Lukashenko, Novikov and Dubko has increased from 2 
to 4 percent since April, while that of Shushkevich has gone 
down from 9.8 to 7.1 percent and Poznyak -- from 5.4 to 4 
percent. 
  The same poll showed that 57.8 percent of the respondents 
welcome the unification of the Russian and Belarusian monetary 
systems, and 77.7 percent favored the creation of a 
Belarusian-Russian financial and economic union. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-38885 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov107_g_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-107 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  1 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

