2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0206162594 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A regular Supreme Council session continued its work 
today in Almaty. The Supreme Council examined and adopted a 
preliminary schedule for examining issues by plenary sessions 
over the coming two months. It introduced changes into 
composition of certain committees and the Control Chamber, 
confirmed a regulation on paying allowances to wages of 
deputies, committee staff, the Control Chamber, Secretariat, and 
the Supreme Council's administration, depending on their length 
of service. Marat Kalmatayev, the chairman of the Committee for 
Law, Order, and Legal Reforms, spoke about the amendments to the 
law on administrative violations. The law was adopted as a 
whole. 
