<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Banks Not Selling Rubles Due to Lack of Supplies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Banks Not Selling Rubles Due to Lack of Supplies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206105994 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Tajik 0500 
GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0206105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Tajik </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Despite the official exchange rate of 1,916 rubles 
[R] for one U.S. dollar, set by the National Bank of Tajikistan 
on 1 June, the rate for selling and buying has already passed 
the R2,000 mark in dealings by the business and state banks of 
Tajikistan. 
  The buying and selling rate for the U.S. dollar set for 
individuals by the National Bank of Tajikistan is R2,000 and 
R2,095 respectively. The rate for the German mark [word 
indistinct] is R1,050 and R1,095. 
  The Tajik Bank Business buys one U.S. dollar for R1,800, 
selling it for R,2063. 
  Due to a lack of supply of rubles to the republic, some 
banks 
have temporarily halted selling rubles to the population. 
  The Vneshekonombank buys one U.S. dollar for R2,050 and one 
German mark for R1,050. 

</TEXT>

