<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Einseln's Resignation Rejected </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Einseln's Resignation Rejected </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0306093594 Tallinn ETA in English 1809 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0306093594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["News Release"] </F>
  [Text] Tallinn, June 2 -- President Lennart Meri has 
refused to accept the resignation of Aleksander Einseln, the 
head of the Estonian Defence Forces, as leaving the position 
vacant would harm Estonia's state and security, the president's 
press office informed ETA on Thursday. Meri had received 
Einseln's letter of resignation on May 31 and had immediately 
responded that the interests of Estonian state prevented him 
from accepting the resignation and that he was to continue his 
service. 
  Einseln's press office released a statement earlier on 
Thursday saying he wanted to resign in protest over being left 
aside by Prime Minister Mart Laar over his defence deal with 
Israel. 
  Einseln is a retired U.S. Army officer who accepted the 
position in defiance of U.S. administration while risking his 
army pension. Einseln is now in Visby attending a Baltic Sea 
defence seminar. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

