<F P=102>   WS0206140494 Tallinn BNS in English 1014 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0206140494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, June 02, BNS -- President Lennart Meri 
today appointed Urmas Arumae as the new justice minister, the 
president's office told BNS. 
  Arumae's candidacy was put forward earlier this morning by 
Prime Minister Mart Laar. 
  Arumae, 37, is a graduate of the Faculty of Law of Tartu 
University. He later graduated from the Estonian Higher School 
of Commerce and obtained his master's degree in international 
business management at the University of San Francisco. After a 
stint as a vice president of Silves Enterprises Ltd., he 
established his own legal aid company, Concordia. Arumae is 
also president of the Estonian Lawyers Union. 

