<F P=103> NC0206202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, June 2 (SNARK)--Armenia is content with the 
idea of the CIS peacekeeping troops' introduction into the zone 
of the Georgian-Abkhazian conflict, said to the journalists 
Levon Zurabyan, the acting press secretary of the Armenian 
President. In his words, the position Armenia takes and 
expressed at the recent forum of the CIS leaders was confirmed 
at the yesterday's meeting of the Armenian President Levon 
Ter-Petrosyan with the CIS Executive Secretary Ivan Korotchenya. 
Mr. Zurabyan refused to inform journalists if Armenia is on the 
desire to send Armenian troops within the peacekeeping forces to 
the region. As for the desire expressed by the Azerbaijani 
authorities to send 400 militaries to the zone of the conflict, 
Levon Zurabyan said that the Armenian authorities consider 
Azerbaijan doesn't bear a relation to it. 

</TEXT>

