<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev Meets With Iranian Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aliyev Meets With Iranian Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   944K1343A Baku AZERBAYDZHAN in Russian 31 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 944K1343A </F>
<F P=104>  Baku AZERBAYDZHAN </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [AZERTADZH report: "Azerbaijani-Iranian Relations Are </F>
Strengthening"] 
  [Text] The continued expansion of relations between 
Azerbaijan and the Islamic Republic of Iran is of great 
significance for both states, and we support the development of 
this cooperation. This was stated by Geydar Aliyev, president of 
the Azerbaijan Republic, on 25 May as he received a delegation 
of the neighboring country headed by Gholam Reza Aqazadeh, 
minister of petroleum of the Islamic Republic of Iran. The 
minister was accompanied on the trip by Ali Abdulalizade, 
governor of Northern Azerbaijan, and other officials. 
  Gholam Reza Aqazadeh conveyed to Geydar Aliyev greetings 
from 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani, president of the Islamic Republic of Iran. 
The head of the Azerbaijani state asked that his respect and 
esteem and best wishes be conveyed to President 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani. Geydar Aliyev observed that a new date for 
his visit to the Islamic Republic of Iran, which would take 
place shortly, had already been determined. The signing by the 
two states of a number of important documents is scheduled. 
  There was in the course of the meeting a comprehensive 
exchange of opinions on a consolidation of economic relations of 
the two countries and the commissioning of latent possibilities 
of their mutual relations and a discussion of topical questions 
of cooperation in the petroleum sphere. 
  Fuad Guliyev, first deputy prime minister of the republic, 
State Counselor Vafa Gulizade, Ali Asgar Nekhavandian, 
ambassador of the Islamic Republic of Iran in Azerbaijan, and 
other officials took part in the meeting. 
  The same day the delegation headed by Gholam Reza Aqazadeh, 
minister of petroleum of the Islamic Republic of Iran, was 
received by Rasul Guliyev, chairman of the Supreme Council of 
the republic. Prospects of an expansion of the two states' 
economic cooperation were discussed in the course of the 
conversation. 
  Ali Asgar Nahavandian, ambassador of the Islamic Republic of 
Iran in Azerbaijan, was present at the meeting. 

</TEXT>

