<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abkhazia Welcomes Upcoming Arrival of CIS Peacemakers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abkhazia Welcomes Upcoming Arrival of CIS Peacemakers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206160894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1351 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206160894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anatoliy Yurkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 2 TASS -- Abkhazia is prepared for 
stationing peacemaking forces, press service of Abkhazian 
Parliament said on Thursday. 
  In accordance with ceasefire agreement signed on May 14, the 
two belligerents are now busy withdrawing their forces from the 
Ingur river banks which form the stand-off line and will soon be 
turned into a buffer zone, where some three thousand peacemakers 
from the CIS member states will be stationed. 
  Visiting Lieutenant Colonel Aleksandr Sokolov, Russian 
deputy 
commander-in-chief of overland troops, met with Abkhazian 
Parliament Speaker Vladislav Ardzinba, the press service said. 
He visited the Gal district, where CIS peacemaking forces will 
be deployed on June 15. 
  Abkhazia considers the peacemakers to be guarantors of peace 
and stability in the region. 

</TEXT>

