<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze Meets London Borough Council Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shevardnadze Meets London Borough Council Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206173394 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1500 
GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0206173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Georgian head of state's press secretariat 
reports that Eduard Shevardnadze, chairman of the Georgian 
parliament and head of state, met representatives of the 
Georgian-English cultural and business center from Great Britain 
-- Trevor Jones, head of the Islington borough council foreign 
relations department, and Anthony Wokes, an economic adviser. 
  The conversation dealt with the activities of the center and 
its future prospects. It has been pointed out that the aims of 
the Georgian-English cultural and business center are to enhance 
interest toward Georgia in Britain, extend friendly relations, 
arrange joint creative work, and reveal and develop mutual 
interests in business. The center has been an initiator of an 
agreement between the Islington municipality of London and 
Tbilisi mayoralty. New business relations will be initiated soon 
between London, Moscow, and Tbilisi. The head of state 
promised the visitors assistance and support. 

</TEXT>

