<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic Accords Likely at Conclusion of Russian Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Economic Accords Likely at Conclusion of Russian Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206190094 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1700 GMT 2 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0206190094 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>
<F P=105>  Latvian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aivars Vovers, under-secretary of state for Eastern 
Affairs at the foreign ministry, and leader of the Latvian group 
of experts at the upcoming joint talks with Russia, said today a 
group of experts from Latvia and Russia will have ten agreements 
on mutual economic cooperation ready for signing. The experts 
have mainly worked in preparation for the visit of Russian Prime 
Minister Chernomyrdin to Latvia, scheduled for late June. It is 
possible that the two countries' leaders will sign the prepared 
agreements on Latvian-Russian cooperation in transportation, on 
mutual protection of capital investments, on handing over to 
Russian ownership of the Amber Coast sanatorium, and on 
cooperation in the protection of industrial property. The 
experts are coordinating the text of a declaration on the trends 
in and prospects for the two countries' economic cooperation. 
During Chernomyrdin's visit they will also discuss questions 
relating to the two countries' prospective cooperation in 
educational, cultural and information areas. In addition, the 
leaders might discuss the issue of the construction of an 
international gas pipeline through Latvia. 

</TEXT>

