<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia's Most Favored Trade Agreement Temporary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia's Most Favored Trade Agreement Temporary </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0306090494 Tallinn BNS in English 1744 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0306090494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Jun 2, BNS -- The most favored nation regime, 
Russia reportedly introduced in trade with Latvia on June 1, is 
a temporary development since Russia reserves the right to 
cancel it any moment it wants to, Aivars Vovers, Latvian Foreign 
Ministry deputy state secretary, told BNS Thursday. 
  The Russian Foreign Ministry informed the Latvian Embassy in 
Moscow about the decision by a note, handed in on May 30. 
  The agreement on the most favored nation status between 
Latvia and Russia is a positive factor for increasing the 
competitiveness of Latvian products, officials said Wednesday. 
  The motion will increase the mutual goods turnover between 
both countries. Export of goods to Russia was very 
disadvantageous to Latvia after March 15 when Russia raised 
import tariffs on a series of products. 
  Russia is still the largest Latvian trade partner. Export of 
Latvian goods to Russia comprises 30 percent of its total export. 
  Russia also expressed a hope in the note that Latvia will 
ratify the signed agreements on the Russian troop withdrawal and 
the social rights of Russian military retirees and their 
families in the near future, the Latvian Foreign Ministry 
reported. 

</TEXT>

