<H3> <TI>   Jobless Rate of 6.6 Percent Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jobless Rate of 6.6 Percent Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0206102794 Tallinn BNS in English 1340 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0206102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Jun 01, BNS -- As many as 101,298 people, or 
6.6 percent of the economically active Latvian residents, were 
looking for jobs on May 31, according to figures from the State 
Statistics Committee. From those, 87,792 have registered 
themselves as unemployed; 34,520 receive allowances; 32,731 are 
long-term unemployed. 
  As reported, the number of job seakers was 102,200 on May 3. 
  State employment service spokeswoman Ilga Upeniece told BNS 
that the decreasing number of unemployed could be explained with 
the beginning of summer. She prognosticated that the figure 
would be up again in autumn. 

</TEXT>

