<H3> <TI>   Britain Supports Ukraine in Crimea Dispute </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Britain Supports Ukraine in Crimea Dispute </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206142594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1343 
GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0206142594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By UKRINFORM correspondent Mikhail Stetsyuk for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Sevastopol, 2 Jun (ITAR-TASS) -- Leaders of the 
Sevastopol state administration and Simon Hemans, the British 
ambassador in Ukraine, discussed the holding of joint events 
dedicated to the 140th anniversary of the Crimean war and the 
organizing of permanent cooperation in tourism. The ambassador 
visited Sevastopol 1-2 June. 
  The guest was received by Ukrainian Navy Commander Vice 
Admiral Vladimir Bezkorovaynyy. The press office of the 
Ukrainian Navy reports that the conversation took place in a 
warm and friendly atmosphere. The commander briefed the 
ambassador on the negotiations regarding the forthcoming 
division of the Black Sea Fleet and the way the building of the 
Ukrainian Navy is progressing. Simon Hemans confirmed the 
position of the British side that the Crimean issue is Ukraine's 
internal affair and that Britain supports Ukraine's policy on 
the Crimea. 

</TEXT>

