<F P=102>   LD0206131794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1101 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206131794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian and Ukrainian experts discussed in 
Sevastopol behind closed doors on Thursday ways of dividing 
naval vessels and infrastructure between Ukraine and Russia, a 
Sevastopol-based source has reported to Interfax. The results 
of these negotiations are to be announced later. 
  Russia was represented at the talks by the Naval Chief of 
Staff Feliks Gromov, the First Deputy Commander of the Black Sea 
Fleet Vitaliy Larionov, and the Head of the Routine Management 
Department Aleksandr Grinko. Negotiating on Ukraine's behalf 
were the Naval Chief of Staff Vladimir Bezkorovayniy, the Head 
of the Routine Management Department Viktor Fomin, and the Naval 
Air Force Commander Nikolay Volodin. 

