<H3> <TI>   Russian Navy Commander on Efforts To Divide Fleet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Navy Commander on Efforts To Divide Fleet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206221794 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1900 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0206221794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Admiral Feliks Gromov, commander in chief of the 
Russian Navy, in a conversation with journalists, said: Efforts 
by a group of naval experts to estimate the fleet's strength, 
particularly its floating capability, is under way. The 
specialists will determine the parameters for the basis of the 
fleet's division, focusing on the categories of ships and their 
technical condition. Feliks Gromov pointed out that this is not 
a meeting of delegations but work done by experts. The work is 
difficult because every ship has to be examined. 
  About his meeting with Admiral Volodymyr Bezkorovaynyy, the 
Ukrainian Naval Forces commander, Feliks Gromov reported that 
their points of view do not coincide, and it is necessary to do 
everything possible to reach a mutual understanding. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

