<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crimean Supreme Council Rejects More Power for Meshkov </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimean Supreme Council Rejects More Power for Meshkov </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206175194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1630 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206175194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today the Crimean parliament excluded from its 
agenda the issue on giving the force of law to the presidential 
decrees on the issues which were not as yet regulated by 
legislation. A total of 51 deputies voted for this decision 
(the total number of deputies in the Crimean parliament is 98). 
  Earlier, Crimean President Yuriy Meshkov had proposed that 
the Crimean parliament give him additional powers. Meshkov said 
his proposals concerning force of law to be given to the 
presidential decrees was of great importance for Crimea which 
would have more possibilities for quick reaction to the changing 
situation in Crimea and around it. 

</TEXT>

