<H3> <TI>   Lvov `Active Vacationers' Leave `To Defend' Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lvov `Active Vacationers' Leave `To Defend' Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306081094 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 2000 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0306081094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- The first group of "active vacationers" from 
Lvov is leaving for Crimea in the next few days, Andriy Shkil, 
leader of the Ukrainian National Assembly-Ukrainian National 
Self-Defense [UNA-UNSO] Lvov branch, told UNIAN. The group will 
be 20-30 strong and its main task will be to "set the stage for 
the arrival of more groups." 
  According to Andriy Shkil, "active vacation groups" in Lvov 
Oblast have already about 200 volunteers on the rolls. But 
UNA-UNSO is unable to dispatch them to Crimea immediately for 
lack of money. "We are busy looking for sponsors of the action 
who would appreciate the need to defend Crimea," Andriy Shkil 
said. 

