<H3> <TI>   Paratroopers Airlifted to Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paratroopers Airlifted to Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306093694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0905 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0306093694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS special correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Sevastopol 3 June TASS -- 127 Ukrainian paratroopers 
arrived on two transport An-26 planes in the Crimea on Friday [3 
June]. TASS learned from local military sources that the planes 
landed at the "Bilbek" airfield situated practically within the 
city of Sevastopol, which is the major base of the Black Sea 
Fleet. 
  The paratroopers are expected to form an airmobile company 
which will guard the airfield and secure airlifting of troops in 
case of necessity, according to the sources. 
  Earlier over 350 Ukrainian national guards were airlifted to 
Sevastopol from Ukraine. According to the Crimean Interior 
Ministry, thay are protecting public order in the city. 

</TEXT>

