<H3> <TI>   1992 Crimean Constitution Still Not in Force </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    1992 Crimean Constitution Still Not in Force </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206175694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1630 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206175694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Crimean President Yuriy Meshkov announced in the 
Crimean parliament that he had not as yet signed the law on 
restoration of the constitutional basis of Crimean statehood 
adopted by the Crimean parliament on May 20. 
  Crimean Minister of Justice Lyubov Yeliseyeva-Bora said that 
the Crimean constitution of May 6, 1992, had not been published 
in media and thus was not enacted. 
  The Crimean constitution of May 6, 1992, provides for 
greater 
autonomy for Crimea within Ukraine and for dual citizenship for 
Crimean inhabitants. 

</TEXT>

