<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Short Circuit at AES Causes False Alarm </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Short Circuit at AES Causes False Alarm </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0306094494 Kiev DEMOKRATYCHNA UKRAYINA in Ukrainian 2 Jun 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU0306094494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev DEMOKRATYCHNA UKRAYINA </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Viktor Krokhmalyuk report: "False Alarm"] </F>
  [Text] At 0220 hours on 29 May, the generator of unit No. 
1 -- the only one at the Khmelnytskyy Atomic Plant -- was 
disconnected from the network as a result of a false triggering 
of the system of protection of the block transformer due to a 
short circuit in the strands of the control cable. The 
automatic system unloaded the reactor installation to the level 
of 10 percent of its nominal load. After the fault was repaired 
power unit No. 1 was reconnected to the network at 0230 hours on 
30 May. There were no violations of the limits or conditions of 
safe operation or changes in radioactivity. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

