<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Proposes Prime Ministerial Candidates </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk Proposes Prime Ministerial Candidates </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206153894 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1245 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206153894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- Ukraine's Supreme Council Presidium held a 
meeting on 1 June attended by the chairmen of the parliament's 
commissions and deputy group leaders. President Leonid Kravchuk 
attended the meeting and proposed candidates for the post of 
Ukraine's prime minister. 
  According to parliamentary sources, the candidates proposed 
by the president include Vitaliy Masol, Pavlo Lazarenko, 
Anatoliy Holubchenko, and Valentyn Symonenko. 
  Other nominees are Acting Prime Minister Yukhym Zvyahilskyy, 
and Ukraine's Liberal Party leader Ihor Markulov. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

