<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commission Formed To Help Bankrupt Workers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commission Formed To Help Bankrupt Workers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206105594 Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network in 
Russian 2300 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0206105594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The republican Union of Entrepreneurs has set up a 
special commission to collect information on enterprises which 
are made bankrupt and are subject to liquidation. The 
commission's task is to help the leaders of such enterprises to 
prepare documents on the enterprises' inability to function and 
their proposals on reorganization. The commission intends to 
address a letter to the president of Kyrgyzstan and establish 
cooperation with the state commission on reorganizing and 
liquidating unprofitable enterprises. 

</TEXT>

