<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition To Hold Rally in Moscow 12 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition To Hold Rally in Moscow 12 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306175194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1603 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0306175194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Moscow government has granted permission to 
several opposition organizations to hold a rally and a march in 
the center of Moscow on June 12 (the anniversary of the adoption 
of the declaration of state sovereignty of the Russian 
Federation.). 
  The rally is allowed gather about 40,000 people. 
  Its slogan will be, "To preserve Russia -- to restore the 
Union!" 
  The rally has been initiated by the National Salvation Front 
(led by Ilya Konstantinov), the Russian Communist Workers Party 
and the Working Russia movement (led by Vladimir Anpilov), the 
Rebirth Liberal Patriotic Party (led by Valeriy Skurlatov), the 
Russian Communist Union (led by Aleksey Prigarin), the All Union 
Bolshevik Communist Party (led by Nina Andreyeva), the Officers 
Union (led by Stanislav Terekhov), the so-called USSR People's 
Deputies Congress Permanent Presidium (chaired by Sazhi 
Umalatova) and other opposition organizations. 
  The initiators were warned against violation of public order 
and reminded of their personal responsibility for this. 

</TEXT>

