<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Renames, Reforms Management Academy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Renames, Reforms Management Academy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606094394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0924 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 6 -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin 
issued a decree on Monday reforming the former Russian 
Management Academy into the Russian State Service Academy, 
directly under the president of the country. 
  The academy will serve as an educational, research, and 
analytical centre devoted to problems of civil servants, the 
president's press service reported on Monday. 
  Yeltsin named Aleksey Mikhaylovich Yemelyanov as 
dean/president of the academy. 

