<H3> <TI>   High Taxes, Low Prices Limiting Oil Exports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    High Taxes, Low Prices Limiting Oil Exports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0506181494 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service in English 
1530 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0506181494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow World Service </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia is not short of oil and is ready to export 
more, the Ministry of Fuel and Energy said in a report prepared 
by its experts. By the beginning of last month the country had 
more than 6.5 million barrels of crude oil unsold. This is more 
than average reserves. Among the factors restricting the sale 
of oil are disproportionately high government taxes and prices. 
As a result, the experts say, even oil exports have become 
ineffective. 

</TEXT>

