<H3> <TI>   Military Social Support Fund Established </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Social Support Fund Established </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306122994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0713 
GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0306122994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostanin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 3 Jun (ITAR-TASS) -- An extra-budgetary fund 
of social support for Russian military servicemen has been 
created at the Main Directorate for the Military Budget and 
Financing of the Russian Defense Ministry. An ITAR-TASS 
correspondent was told of this today by Colonel Aleksandr 
Goncharov of the Defense Ministry's information and press 
department. 
  He said that the money will come from the activities of the 
military insurance company. According to a Russian Federation 
Defense Ministry directive, it will be used to stage military- 
patriotic and cultural events and to organize meetings with the 
participants of wars and veterans of the armed forces. It is 
also envisioned to use the money from the extra-budgetary fund 
to pay for the treatment of servicemen and their families, to 
provide gratuitous financial assistance to large families, and 
particularly servicemen in need, and as subsidies to public 
catering enterprises located in officers' houses and officers' 
clubs. 

</TEXT>

