<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soskovets: ROK Relations Should Not Harm DPRK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Soskovets: ROK Relations Should Not Harm DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0406125394 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service in English 
1100 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0406125394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow World Service </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Oleg Soskovets, the Russian first deputy chairman of 
the Council of Ministers, believes that the relations between 
Russia and South Korea should develop not to the detriment to 
contacts with North Korea. I wouldn't like to talk of sharp 
confrontation with North Korea, Soskovets told a RIA 
correspondent. 
  Russian firms and enterprises display noticeable interest in 
North Korea. The former USSR built their many enterprises and 
production capacities. This is our potential machine -- the 
metallurgic and energy market -- and it is not expedient to lose 
it for political reasons. At the same time the deputy prime 
minister pointed out that North Korea should unconditionally 
comply with the UN demands on nuclear power engineering. 

</TEXT>

