<H3> <TI>   Greek Minister Hands Yeltsin Message From Papandreou </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Greek Minister Hands Yeltsin Message From Papandreou </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306114894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0929 
GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0306114894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 3 Jun (ITAR-TASS) -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin today received Karolos Papoulias, representing the 
president of the European Union [Council] and Greek foreign 
minister, who conveyed a message from Greek Prime Minister 
Andreas Papandreou, who [currently] presides over the EU. 
According to the Russian president's press service, the message 
expresses the conviction that preparations for an agreement on 
Russia's partnership and cooperation with the EU will soon come 
to a successful conclusion, and the agreement could be signed 
during the meeting of the EU heads of state and government on 
the island of Corfu 24-25 June. A. Papandreou expressed hope 
that the Russian president might be able to sign the agreement. 
  Boris Yeltsin said that, if the agreement with the EU has 
been duly prepared by that time, he could attend the signing. 
  During the conversation, according to the Russian 
president's 
press service, several aspects of Russian-Greek relations were 
discussed. 

