<H3> <TI>   Kolesnikov Talks With Syria on Military Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kolesnikov Talks With Syria on Military Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606083994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0823 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606083994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Dmitriy Zelenin] </F>
  [Text] Beirut June 6 TASS -- Russian Chief of Staff, Army 
General Mikhail Kolesnikov, on Sunday held talks in Damascus 
with his Syrian counterpart, General Hikmat al-Shihabi. 
According to officials, the two chiefs of staff discussed 
"cooperation between the Syrian and Russian armies in the 
interests of the two friendly countries". The sources said that 
high-ranking Syrian and Russian officers were present, but no 
other details of the talks were disclosed. 
  Mikhail Kolesnikov arrived in the Syrian capital on Sunday 
and is due to meet Syrian Defence Minister, Mustafa Talas on 
Monday. The visit was arranged in pursuance of the accords 
reached during the negotiations in Damascus in April with the 
Russian government delegation led by First Deputy Chairman of 
the Russian Government Oleg Soskovets. 

