<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Concerned by Israeli Attack on Lebanon </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Concerned by Israeli Attack on Lebanon </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306160094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1451 
GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0306160094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 3 June -- Moscow is concerned about the 
latest outbreak of military actions in the zone adjacent to the 
Lebanese-Israeli frontier, a Foreign Ministry spokesman said 
here today. 
  He said that as a result of an Israeli aviation attack on a 
Hizballah base, there were many Lebanese casualties, and the 
territorial sovereignty of Lebanon had been violated. In turn, 
areas in northern Israel were subjected to dangerous fire. 
  "These alarming events cast a shadow over the continuation 
of 
Arab-Israeli dialogue and reconfirm the need for stepping up the 
comprehensive search for political solutions," the statement by 
the repesentative of the Russian diplomatic department said. 
"Only at the negotiating table can and should agreements be 
reached guaranteeing both the restoration of the territorial 
integrity of Lebanon and the mutual security of this state and 
Israel, and guaranteeing that there is no dangerous escalation 
of violence." 
  As co-sponsor of the Near East peace process, Russia calls 
upon all sides "to display maximum restraint and common sense 
and to be guided in their actions by the long-term interests of 
establishing a stable and just peace in the region." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

