<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish General's Anti-Russian Remarks Questioned </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish General's Anti-Russian Remarks Questioned </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306173294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1708 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0306173294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow June 3 TASS -- A spokesman for the Russian 
Foreign ministry protested today against anti-Russian statements 
of the Turkish military chief. 
  Turkish media recently cited Gueres as saying that Russia is 
an even bigger threat to Turkey now than it was during the cold 
war. The general accused Moscow of expansionist desires in 
relation to the Caucasus region, Ukraine, and even the Balkan 
states. 
  Such statements "fundamentally contradict the agreement 
reached between the Russian and Turkish higher leadership that 
their relations have entered a new level of friendly 
partnership", the spokesman said on Friday. 
  He mentioned the many announcements made by Turkish 
President 
Suleyman Demirel, Prime Minister Tansu Ciller, and other Turkish 
leaders, which expressed satisfaction that Russian-Turkish 
relations have entered a new era and are now based on mutual 
interests and the spirit of cooperation. 
  "The Russian side would like to hope that the statements 
made 
by Gueres do not reflect the point of view of Turkey's political 
leadership, and Russia bases its policy on the assumption that 
Ankara is just as interested as Moscow is in the further 
development of Russian-Turkish relations and multilateral 
cooperation", the Foreign Ministry spokesman declared. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

