<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soskovets To Visit Malaysia To Sign MiG Deal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Soskovets To Visit Malaysia To Sign MiG Deal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0506085894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0717 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0506085894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Oleg Velichko] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 5 -- A government delegation led by 
First Vice-Premier Oleg Soskovets will fly to Malaysia for a 
two-day visit this afternoon. The main event of the coming trip 
is the signing of a contract on June 7 to sell Malaysia 18 
Russian MiG-29 fighters. 
  The Russian delegation will discuss a package of bilateral 
economic issues with Malaysian Premier Mahathir Mohamed and his 
cabinet members in the Malaysian capital Kuala Lumpur. It is 
also planned that the delegation will be received by the 
Malaysian supreme head of state. 
  ITAR-TASS learnt at the Russian Government's office that the 
above-mentioned contract has been agreed upon. It is worth 615 
million U.S. dollars. According to Malaysian representatives, 
20- 25 per cent of the sum will be paid with palm oil, necessary 
for various industries. 
  The first fighter will be delivered next April. The 
implementation of the entire project is planned for a 25-year 
period and provides for creating infrastructure in Malaysia, 
necessary for the operation of MiG fighters. 
  The two countries plan to build in Malaysia a technical 
centre to service aircraft. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

