<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nationalities Minister Meets N. Ossetian, Ingush Presidents </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nationalities Minister Meets N. Ossetian, Ingush Presidents </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606104494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1007 
GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0606104494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz, 6 Jun (ITAR-TASS) -- During his trip to 
the North Caucasus, Nikolay Yegorov, the Russian minister for 
affairs of nationalities and regional policy, aims to 
familiarize himself on the spot with the latest situation in the 
state of emergency zone and decide how to implement the 
presidential decrees and the resolutions of the Russian 
Government. On Monday, he arrived in Vladikavkaz, where he met 
with North Ossetia President Akhsarbek Galazov. 
  This afternoon Nikolay Yegorov, Vladimir Lozovoy, head of 
the 
interim administration, and a group of representatives from 
federal ministries and departments, flew out to Nazran where 
Yegorov is to meet with Ruslan Aushev, president of Ingushetia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

