<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ingush President on Situation in State of Emergency Zone </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ingush President on Situation in State of Emergency Zone </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306194694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1810 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0306194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The situation in the state of emergency zone will 
never stabilize if the Interim Administration on Ingush and 
South Ossetian territory and Vladikavkaz ignore the decree on 
the return of deported Ingush to their places of permanent 
residence issued by the Russian president. This was stated by 
Ingush President Ruslan Aushev at a press conference in Nazran 
today. The press conference was held on the decision of the 
Russian Federation Council which had confirmed the presidential 
decree on extending the state of emergency in the zone of the 
inter-ethnic conflict until July 31. 
  Aushev said that the return of Ingush refugees would depend 
on how efficiently the Interim Administration headed by Vladimir 
Lozovoy would perform. 

</TEXT>

