<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moscow Authorities Seek To Clear Refugees From Oblast </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow Authorities Seek To Clear Refugees From Oblast </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0606093994 Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA in Russian 2 Jun 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM0606093994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Refugee? Get Running!"] </F>
  [Text] In Moscow and Moscow Oblast the militia have 
started "hunting" refugees from countries of the near abroad and 
certain Arab regions. Organs, following a decree from the 
Moscow City Government, are to locate citizens in this category 
and unambiguously "request" that they leave Moscow Oblast. 
  There are currently 6,000 refugees (it is thought) in the 
city. Not one of them is registered, since there is no relevant 
legislation covering this. These people are not even entitled 
to look for work or seek hospital treatment. Consequently, they 
are often forced into crime in order to earn money for food. 
  Incidentally, the other day the Russian Federation 
president's Human Rights Commission prepared a report, which 
nobody has as yet examined, on the need to grant automatic 
Russian citizenship to any refugee who requests it. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

