<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soskovets Views Tatarstan Defense Industry </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Soskovets Views Tatarstan Defense Industry </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   944F0764A Kazan RESPUBLIKA TATARSTAN in Russian 2 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 944F0764A </F>
<F P=104>  Kazan RESPUBLIKA TATARSTAN </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Report by R. Rashitov: "Defense Industry Problems at the </F>
Center of Attention"] 
  [Text] Topical questions regarding joint measures for 
stabilization of the situation at defense industry enterprises, 
worked out by the Governments of the Russian Federation and 
Republic of Tatarstan, were discussed during the consultations 
held in Kazan by O.N. Soskovets, first deputy chairman of the 
Government of Russia, and Tatarstan Prime Minister M.G. Sabirov. 
  The participants in the consultations--directors of a number 
of military-industrial complex large industrial 
enterprises--discussed the problems of preservation and 
improvement of the defense industry's scientific and 
technological potential, and speeding up the production of 
civilian goods at these enterprises that would be both 
competitive and affordable for the population. 
  An agreement was reached to provide conversion credits, tax 
preferences, placing long-term orders, and gradual transfer of 
housing and social-cultural facilities into the ownership of, 
and maintenance by, local bodies of executive authority. It was 
pointed out to defense industry enterprise directors that they 
have to boost their commercial activities aimed at selling the 
products they produce, including exporting them. 
  O.N. Soskovets and M.G. Sabirov visited production shops and 
sections of aviation and motor-building production associations, 
where they were shown samples of output, and talked to workers 
and technical-engineering personnel. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

