<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Attacks on Novosibirsk Bankers Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Attacks on Novosibirsk Bankers Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0606103994 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 2 Jun 94 
First Edition p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PM0606103994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report: "In the Mafia's `Sights'"] </F>
  [Text] A Novosibirsk couple have ended up on the operating 
table as a result of a grenade thrown through their apartment 
window on the night of 31 May. The injured couple are widely 
known in the city: Yekaterina Zhabotinskaya is head of the 
Central Bank of Russia's chief branch in Novosibirsk Oblast. 
Vladimir Zhabotinskiy is deputy director of a firm. According 
to information from the hospital, both sustained multiple 
wounds. Following operations, there are no fears for their lives. 
  Criminal proceedings have been instituted and an 
investigation is under way. 
  This attempt continues the chain of crimes connected with 
leaders of the local branch of the Central Bank. Its former 
chief, Vasiliy Cheplakov, has twice found himself in the 
criminals' "sights." He was doused with acid, then shot, but 
luckily the bullet missed. 
  "I know full well that I will be the criminals' next victim, 
because I am not convenient for a lot of people," Nikolay 
Beloslyudtsev, deputy chief of the Central Bank branch, said in 
an interview with ITAR-TASS. He expressed strong indignation 
over the fact that the two attempts on Cheplakov's life remain 
unsolved. In his opinion, "the law-enforcement organs are 
dozing." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

