<F P=102>   MK0306131094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 3 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> MK0306131094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Irina Vladykina report under the "Ornithology" rubric: </F>
"Zhirinovskiy's "Falcons" Build Their Nest in the Urals. 
Liberal Democratic Party of Russia's Universities in 
Yekaterinburg"] 
  [Text] A reception was arranged in Yekaterinburg the other 
day for the opening of an LDPR [Liberal Democratic Party of 
Russia] headquarters in the city. According to LDPR Urals 
coordinator Vyacheslav Senko, the local organization numbers 
around 500 Zhirinovskiyites up and down the Urals. At the 
moment they are busy opening their own university and setting up 
a scientific research laboratory to study anomalous phenomena. 
True enough, under Mr. Zhirinovskiy's instructions, the party's 
membership and the presence of money in the party till cannot be 
divulged. But journalists have managed to find out that 
"himself" is planning a visit to Yekaterinburg in June. 
  After power ends up in the hands of Vladimir Volfovich 
[Zhirinovskiy], they were told at the Yekaterinburg LDPR 
headquarters, 30 seats in the State Duma would be made available 
to the Urals organization. In the meantime, the local 
organization of the Zhirinovskiy party sets itself the task of 
organizing a massive admission of new members into its ranks, 
and to start its own "URALS" newspaper. 

</TEXT>

