<H3> <TI>   Karelia Temporarily Halts Privatization </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karelia Temporarily Halts Privatization </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0406133194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0716 
4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0406133194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Zlobin] </F>
  [Text] Petrozavodsk, 4 Jun -- The head of the Karelian 
government, Viktor Stepanov, has issued an instruction halting 
the privatization in Karelia of buildings and installations that 
are the republic's state property. Leasing them out has also 
been banned. 
  These measures are temporary, the document says. They have 
been taken to bring order to the questions of privatization. A 
special commission has been set up to check the use of buildings 
that are state property. The commission has been given until 15 
July to present proposals on correcting the privatization 
process in Karelia. 

</TEXT>

