<H3> <TI>   Kebich Addresses Law Enforcement Agencies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kebich Addresses Law Enforcement Agencies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0606090094 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1715 
GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0606090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, the first session of the Belarusian Cabinet 
of Ministers' Coordinating Council of Law Enforcement Agencies 
-- on combating corruption and crime -- was held. National law 
enforcement agencies heads, chairmen of oblasts and a range of 
city and rayon executive committees participated in this 
meeting. Prime Minister Vyachaslaw Kebich, chairman of the 
Coordinating Council, said that combating crime is a key issue. 
This is a very important social issue, which in equal measure 
concerns both government and residents of the Republic. In the 
prime minister's opinion, in order to ensure personal freedom 
and self-confidence, not only new approaches by law enforcement 
agencies should be introduced but a range of everyday pressing 
problems of the citizenry should be resolved as well. 

</TEXT>

