<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Round of Talks on 14th Army Withdrawal 7-8 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Round of Talks on 14th Army Withdrawal 7-8 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0306144594 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2100 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0306144594 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 1/6/1994 -- The ninth round of 
the Moldovan-Russian negotiations concerning the status and 
terms of withdrawal of the 14th Russian Army from Moldovan 
territory will be held on 7 and 8 June in Moscow, stated to BASA 
Ion Nastac, head of the press secretariat of the Ministry of 
Defence. The official Moldovan delegation will be headed by 
Nicolae Osmochescu, vice-minister of foreign affairs, specified 
the cited source. Colonel Nicolae Tudureanu will lead the group 
of military experts. With the approval of both Moldovan and 
Russian delegations, representatives of Tiraspol will be allowed 
to attend the negotiations. The previous round of talks was 
held in March 1994 in Chisinau. The negotiators did not agree 
on the terms of withdrawal of the Russian armed forces from 
Moldova, for the Russian delegation wanted Moldova to grant 
Dniester a spectral juridical status in conjunction with its 
withdrawal. At this meeting the Moldovan delegation was headed 
by Anatol Taran, former ambassador of Moldova to Moscow. 

</TEXT>

