<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tiraspol Public Organizations Union Rejects Market Economy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tiraspol Public Organizations Union Rejects Market Economy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0306194394 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2149 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0306194394 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 2/6/1994 -- The Union of Public 
Organizations Parties and Movements organized a rally yesterday 
in Tiraspol. Professor V. Yakovlev, former deputy of the 
Moldovan Parliament known for his orthodox communist views, is 
the leader of the union. V. Yakovlev and representatives of 
other political organizations opposed the promotion of market 
economic reforms in Dniester and the introduction of private 
ownership of land and privatization in general. Appeals to 
restore the Soviet Union could be heard during the rally. 
Yakovlev declared that recently an initiative group had been 
created to bring about the creation of a union of unrecognized 
states. It is assumed that alongside Dniester, Abkhazia, 
Karabakh and another breakaway regions will be members of this 
union. The rally attracted about 1,000 people, most of whom 
were elderly. People carried red flags and sang the USSR's 
anthem. Local observers note that the rally was not obstructed 
by militia although the emergency state prolonged by Igor 
Smirnov [Dniester president] forbids such manifestations. 

</TEXT>

