<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tiraspol Officials Blame Chisinau for Blocking Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tiraspol Officials Blame Chisinau for Blocking Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0406174594 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1925 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0406174594 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tiraspol BASAPRESS, 3/6/1994 -- The Dniester 
Republic's delegation will not disregard the referendum which 
expresses the independence of the Dniester Republic's people and 
its right to individual statehood, stated today to Tiraspol 
Radio Ana Volkova, former member of the Dniester delegation 
attending the negotiations on granting a special juridical 
status to the eastern districts. Nicolae Andronic, Moldovan 
deputy speaker of parliament, stated to Tiraspol Radio on 31 May 
that the Tiraspol leaders are to be blamed for jeopardizing the 
settlement of the Dniester conflict. Concerning these 
statements, Volkova mentioned that the Moldovan Parliament's 
statements contain "inaccuracies or even distortions of events." 
Volkova said that Andronic's statements are unfounded. She 
mentioned that it was the Tiraspol representatives who proposed 
a plan for a confederation in Moldova. Volkova said that if 
Chisinau had accepted that plan, the Dniester conflict would 
have been solved long ago. Volkova added that it was the 
Moldovan delegation who left the negotiations "arguing that the 
commission's members were on vacation or that the parliament was 
dissolved." 

</TEXT>

