<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   More Than 5 Million Tonnes of Grain To Be Exported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More Than 5 Million Tonnes of Grain To Be Exported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606081794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0632 
GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0606081794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Fedor Ignatov, ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Alma-ata [Almaty], 6 Jun (ITAR-TASS) -- In 
accordance with intergovernment agreements, Kazakhstan is to 
supply over 5 million [metric] tonnes of grain to other 
countries this year. Three million tonnes is to go to 
Uzbekistan, while Belarus, Kirghizia [Kyrgyzstan], and Iran are 
to get 500,000 tonnes each. Grain from Kazakhstan will also go 
to Tajikistan, Moldavia [Moldova], and Turkmenia [Turkmenistan]. 
  Individual producers will contest the right to export grain 
in auctions to be staged by the Kazakhstan International 
Exchange and the Republic's commodity exchanges. A resolution 
adopted on this subject by the Cabinet of Ministers notes that 
exported grain will be exempt from customs duty. 

</TEXT>

