<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discuss Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Discuss Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0506041094 Seoul YONHAP in English 0303 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0506041094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tashkent, 4 June (YONHAP) -- South Korea and 
Uzbekistan will promote partnership and cooperation by combining 
Korea's development experience and industrial technology and 
Uzbekistan's rich natural resources and industrious labor. 
  This was agreed on in a summit between Presidents Kim 
Yong-sam and Islam Karimov in the state guest house Saturday 
afternoon, President Kim's spokesman Chu Ton-sik said. 
  President Karimov, welcoming South Korean corporate 
investment in his country, agreed to provide as much legal and 
administrative support as possible to Korean corporations 
investing in Uzbekistan. 
  Kim said South Korea would support the Central Asian 
country's economic development program, while pursuing a policy 
to promote economic cooperation between the two countries, 
according to the spokesman. 
  On Sunday, Kim is to visit a farm run by an ethnic Korean 
near Samarkand, the old capital of Uzbekistan, and attend a 
reception for ethnic Koreans hosted by the Tashkent province 
governor. 

</TEXT>

