<H3> <TI>   New Deputy Foreign Minister Appointed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Deputy Foreign Minister Appointed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306143994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1221 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0306143994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tigran Liloyan] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan June 3 TASS -- Eduard Zuloyan, 37, has been 
appointed Armenian deputy foreign minister and included in a 
state delegation at the talks with the Russian Federation. 
  Zuloyan graduated from the Yerevan Polytechnical Institute. 
He worked in the Yerevan Physics Institute and the Armenian 
State Security Committee, and was a foreign affairs adviser to 
the republican minister of transport and communications. Since 
July last year he has been heading the military-political 
department at the Armenian Foreign Ministry. 
