<HT>    "drsov108_r_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-108 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  5 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armenians Reportedly Preparing New Offensive </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armenians Reportedly Preparing New Offensive </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0506194194 Baku TURAN in English 1703 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0506194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku (June 4) TURAN -- According to Azerbaijan's 
Defense Ministry a relative calm is observed along the front 
line. 
  At the same time, having crossed the state border of 
Azerbaijan and having started a new offensive towards Kemerli 
(Kazakh region of Azerbaijan) Armenian forces in result of 
fights mastered height Melicli, which is of strategical 
importance. Turan was told by local sources that remaining 
loyal to cease fire agreement Azerbaijan did not answered to 
this military actions of Armenia. 
  Military sources told Turan that Armenian Military forces 
continue to gather military hardware and soldiers on the north 
front. 

</TEXT>

