<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Over 100 Armenians Killed, Wounded in Nakhichevan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Over 100 Armenians Killed, Wounded in Nakhichevan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0306162694 Baku Radio Baku International Service in Azeri 
1300 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0306162694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Radio Baku International Service </F>
<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The AZERBAIJAN NEWS SERVICE AND PRESS AGENCY 
[AZERBAYCAN NEWS SERVICE, PRESS AGENTLIGI] has reported that the 
situation between the Armenian and Azerbaijani forces has 
worsened over the past few days. A complex situation has 
emerged in Sadarak Rayon in the Nakhichevan Autonomous Republic, 
which is a part of Azerbaijan. The Armenian aggressors have 
made several attempts to attack important heights in that area 
over the past few days. Consequently, some 100 Armenian soldiers 
have been killed or wounded. The enemy units have been forced 
to retreat to their previous positions. Several Armenian tanks 
and other military vehicles have been hit in the clashes. 
Meanwhile, positional fighting continues on other parts of the 
front line. 

</TEXT>

