<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Fire Warning Shots at Crowd Attacking Candidate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Fire Warning Shots at Crowd Attacking Candidate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0506191094 Tbilisi First Program Television Network in 
Georgian 1700 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0506191094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi First Program Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A Georgian Information Agency correspondent has 
learned from competent sources that a meeting was held in 
Chkhorotsku yesterday between voters and a candidate 
representing the Traditionalists' Union. 
  About 70 voters attended the meeting, which was addressed by 
Akaki Asatiani, chairman of the Traditionalists' Union. He used 
offensive terms when referring to the policy of the present 
government, to Eduard Shevardnadze, and to rayon police 
employees, whom he called traitors because they served the 
authorities. 
  This prompted a negative reaction from participants in the 
meeting. A large proportion of them left the building in 
protest following a heated argument and oral exchange. After a 
short while, a group of outraged citizens moved toward the 
building while the visitors were still there. In order to avoid 
a serious incident, the police fired several warning shots in 
the air. The chairman of the Traditionalists' Union and union 
members were forced to leave the building and then the rayon. 
  Criminal proceedings have been instituted in connection with 
the incident. An investigation is under way. 

</TEXT>

