<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM correspondent Mikhail Stetsyuk-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Sevastopol 3 June TASS -- Military experts are 
completing lists of ships of the Black Sea Fleet to be divided 
between Russia and Ukraine, journalists learned although no 
official reports for the media are available. 
  The talks between Russian and Ukrainian military experts 
which have been going on for three days, were attended today by 
Ukrainian Deputy Foreign Minister Boris Tarasyuk, Vice-Premier 
Valeriy Shmarov and Deputy Ukrainian Defence Minister Ivan 
Bizhan, who arrived in Sevastopol on Friday to take part in the 
work of groups of military experts. 
  As for the division of naval bases and coastal 
infrastructure,the sides have been outlining their positions 
yet. These problems are expected to be high on the agenda of 
talks scheduled in Kiev on 8-9 June. 
  Yuriy Dubinin, special envoy of the Russian Foreign 
Ministry, 
has failed to arrive in Sevastopol today for unknown reasons, 
although he had been expected since yesterday. However, 
problems of the location of the fleets' bases are not likely to 
be discussed in Sevastopol without representatives of the 
Russian Government. 

</TEXT>

