<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks Held With Russia on Gas Debt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks Held With Russia on Gas Debt </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306172794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1619 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0306172794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko, </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev 3 June TASS -- Delegations from Russia and 
Ukraine are holding talks in Kiev today on the settlement of 
Ukraine's debt to Russia for supplied gas. 
  Chairman of the Ukrainian State Committee for Gas and Oil 
Supplies, Mikhail Kovalko, said that this year, Ukraine already 
owes the Russian Gasprom joint stock society a considerable sum 
of money in hard currency. The overall debt has been estimated 
at $850 million. "Today's talks with our Russian partners are 
very important," Kovalko said. The sides are expected to look 
into political problems connected with the further development 
of gas pipe line systems in Russia and Ukraine and an increase 
in exports of Russian gas to countries of Western Europe, 
Kovalko said. 
  "Chairman of the board of the Gasprom joint stock society, 
Rem Vyakhirev, told ITAR-TASS that they regard financial 
difficulties faced by their Ukrainian colleagues with 
understanding. Vyakhirev said that they approved of Ukraine's 
proposal to repay part of the debt at the expense of 
construction of houses for Gasprom workers in Russia. "Today, 
we intend to discuss the terms of construction and evaluate its 
cost," Vyakhirev said. "We are also interested in a more 
efficient use of Ukraine's gas pipe line system for exports of 
Russian gas to Western countries," Vyakhirev said. 
  Later in the day, the sides are expected to sign a contract 
on further cooperation in this field. 

</TEXT>

