<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks Conclude </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks Conclude </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0406142794 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1330 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0406142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- Two-day talks between the delegations of the 
Russian joint stock company Gazprom and Ukraine's gas industry 
and government officials ended on 4 June. A schedule for the 
Ukrainian consumers to service their debt for Russian gas was 
agreed. An accord was reached on creating favorable conditions 
for contracts for gas deliveries to be concluded directly by 
Ukraine's enterprises and Russia's Gazprom, as well as on 
commercial firms participating in the settlement of the debt. 
An agreement was signed on cooperation in expanding and 
revamping transit gas pipelines in Ukraine. To that end, a 
joint stock venture is to be set up by the end of this year. 
Agreement was reached on the transfer of 15 to 30 percent of 
the shares in Odessa's port works to the Russian joint stock 
company Gazprom as authorized by Ukraine's State Property Fund. 

</TEXT>

