<H3> <TI>   EU Envoy Says Agricultural Aid Matter of Priority </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EU Envoy Says Agricultural Aid Matter of Priority </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206211794 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 2000 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206211794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev [no dateline as received] -- Today, experts 
from the European Union's [EU] Technical Aid Program to CIS 
Countries (TACIS) held a news conference on assistance to 
Ukraine in agricultural production and food distribution. 
  Under the TACIS program, a total of 150 million ECU 
[European 
currency unit] has been provided for Ukraine since 1991. It was 
agriculture, however, that Luis Moreno, EU ambassador to 
Ukraine, described as a priority aspect of the program that 
mostly deals with consultative and technical assistance. Around 
100 million ECU worth of food will be given to Ukraine. Luis 
Moreno expressed the hope that the volume of agricultural 
production in Ukraine will, in 10 years, be the second largest 
in Europe. 
  EU experts Stuart Lisor and Patrik Pyusemye spoke about the 
implementation in various areas of Ukraine of aid programs to 
modernize the infrastructure of baby food manufacture and 
production of meat, milk, vegetables, fruit, animal feed, the 
improvement of wholesale and retail food distribution, and the 
privatization of food stores. 

</TEXT>

