<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Clinton Discuss DPRK `Nuclear Problem' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin, Clinton Discuss DPRK `Nuclear Problem' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306165494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1629 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0306165494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow June 3 TASS -- Presidents Boris Yeltsin and 
Bill Clinton had a telephone conversation today, the 
presidential press service reports. 
  The Russian state head "informed Bill Clinton of Russian 
ideas on settlement of the North Korean `nuclear problem,' 
including the idea of a multilateral conference, in development 
of his conversations with South Korean President Kim Yong-sam on 
Thursday." 
  The presidents agreed to instruct their experts to analyze 
these issues and prepare corresponding proposals, said the press 
service. 

</TEXT>

