<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Turkish President's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on Turkish President's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Arrives, Met by Snegur </H4>

<F P=102> AU0306144494 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2100 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0306144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 1/6/1994 -- An official 
delegation of the Republic of Turkey arrived this morning on a 
special plane from Kiev. The delegation is headed by the 
Turkish President Suleyman Demirel. It consists of more than 
140 Turkish ministers, Parliament members, businessmen and 
journalists. The delegation was welcomed at the airport by 
President Mircea Snegur, leaders of the Government and 
Parliament and other officials. After a military ceremony 
Demirel and Snegur made some short declarations for the press. 
The Turkish President mentioned the importance of the relations 
between Turkey and Moldova, both in the international and 
regional transformations occurring in the Black Sea basin. 
Referring to the Gagauz population of Turkish origin Demirel 
expressed his hope that the proportion of Gagauz people in the 
general development of Moldova will considerably increase. 
President Snegur declared that taking into consideration the 
cultural affinity between Turks and Gagauzians, both presidents 
will visit southern Moldova where they will get acquainted with 
the life style and preoccupations of the Gagauzians." Snegur 
added that the parties will sign some agreements of 
collaboration in the fields of culture, transportation, 
agriculture, crime control, etc. The main document to be signed 
is the Treaty on Friendship and Collaboration between Moldova 
and Turkey. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

