<H3> <TI>   Azeri Forces Sustain Losses in Attack 3-4 June </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Azeri Forces Sustain Losses in Attack 3-4 June </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0406170794 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 
1500 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0406170794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The situation has again worsened on the northeast 
section of the border between Azerbaijan and Armenia. Our 
correspondent has the details: 
  [Unidentified correspondent] The press service of Armenia's 
Defense Ministry says that on the night of 4 June, a motorized 
infantry battalion of the Azerbaijani Army, supported by armored 
vehicles, attacked positions of Armenia's territorial defense 
forces close to the village of (Davik) in Noyemberyansiky rayon. 
Azerbaijani sub-units managed to move onto Armenian territory 
and even to progress toward the rayon center of Noyemberyan. 
However, after a regrouping of forces and the arrival of 
reinforcements, the aggressor was beaten back to its original 
positions. Azerbaijan's Army lost around one infantry platoon 
[as heard] and one infantry combat vehicle. The Armenian losses 
are not yet known. 

</TEXT>

