<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rutskoy, Others To Establish `Democratic Center' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rutskoy, Others To Establish `Democratic Center' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0406183994 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 
1800 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0406183994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Regional branches of the Democratic Party of Russia, 
the Party of Russian Unity and Accord, the Social Democratic 
Party, and the Social Democratic People's Party of Aleksandr 
Rutskoy are hoping to set up a united democratic center in 
Moscow. This issue was tackled today by the steering committee 
of the united center. 
  Ilya Roytman, one of the center's organizers, said that the 
center will become a coordinating body, able to identify and 
support united democratic candidates in the run-up to the next 
election. 

</TEXT>

