<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   To Examine Crimean Issue 13-16 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    To Examine Crimean Issue 13-16 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0506162494 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1300 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0506162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Max van der Stoel, CSCE high commissioner for 
minorities, has been visiting Ukraine since 31 May until 4 June. 
The aim of his visit was to study the situation in the Republic 
of Crimea, which took shape after its Supreme Council adopted a 
decision on restoring the 6 May 1992 wording of the Crimean 
constitution and also to work out recommendations concerning the 
participation of the CSCE in its settlement. 
  During the visit, Mr. Max van der Stoel had meetings with 
President Leonid Kravchuk, high-level officials of Ukraine and 
Crimea, and representatives of public organizations. The high 
commissioner highly assessed the balanced stand of Ukraine's 
leadership, based exceptionally on the provisions of the 
Constitution of Ukraine in its approaches to the solution of the 
Crimean issue. 
  Max van der Stoel emphasized the necessity of abiding by the 
fundamental principles of the CSCE, especially such principles 
as ensuring territorial integrity and inviolability of borders 
and also the necessity of the soonest possible settlement of the 
situation on legal principles. 
  The issue on the situation that took shape as a result of 
the 
actions by the Crimean leadership and the possible promotion of 
its solution on the part of CSCE is to be considered at a 
sitting of the CSCE committee of Senior officials, which will 
take place in Prague on 13-16 June. 

</TEXT>

