BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 3 Jun [date as received] -- Lieutenant General 
Lev Hnatenko, the chief of armaments staff, made public new 
state programs for designing, manufacturing, and repairing 
armaments for the Armed Forces of Ukraine. The Malyshev plant 
in Kharkov will build most sophisticated tanks, the Antonov 
plant in Kiev will build aircraft, the "Arsenal" plant in Kiev 
and "Pivdenmash" in Dnepropetrovsk will manufacture small fire 
arms. Ten new naval ships are being built and modern 
"air-to-air" missiles are being designed. 

