<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kuchma Sets Out Election Platform </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kuchma Sets Out Election Platform </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306153594 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1220 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0306153594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Odessa -- Ukrainian presidential candidate Leonid 
Kuchma outlined his platform again at a meeting with the cadets 
of a local militia school on 2 June. "Last year I signed a joint 
statement with [Russian prime minister] Chernomyrdin and 
[Belarusian prime minister] Kebich on the creation of an 
economic union to lift customs barriers," he said. But the 
Ukrainian media accused me of pro-Russian sentiments, and the 
eastern and southern regions for some reason did not support me, 
although they should have...." 
  Leonid Kuchma clarified his position on the Crimean issue: 
"The Crimeans must be given greater freedom within Ukraine." 
  The candidate believes that everyone must take the blame for 
the Belavezha "crime" [reference to the formation of the CIS], 
and that the Black Sea Fleet should be sold to Russia because it 
"has strategic interests in the Black Sea" which it will not 
renounce, while "Ukraine is incapable of maintaining the fleet." 
  After the meeting, Oleksandr Mayorov, general secretary of 
the Central Committee of the Renewed Communist Party of Ukraine 
told UNIAN: "We communists will vote for Leonid Kuchma." 

</TEXT>

