<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pro-Communists Want Belovezh Authors Removed From Politics </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pro-Communists Want Belovezh Authors Removed From Politics </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306193794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1810 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0306193794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pro-communist forces are seeking to remove from the 
political scene the three men who were the authors of the 1991 
Belovezh agreements of 1991 on establishment of the CIS, 
Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk said today. He added that 
following this the pro-communist forces would annul the Belovezh 
agreements and restore the USSR. 
  Commenting on the political situation in Ukraine, Kravchuk 
stated that the decision that the presidential and local 
elections take place this June could completely destroy 
executive power in the country. 
  Kravchuk said he could have decided not to run for 
presidency. However, he suggested that those who will take part 
in the presidential race could in two days eliminate everything 
which had been created, if one of the present candidates is 
elected president. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

