<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rukh Decides To Form Shadow Cabinet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rukh Decides To Form Shadow Cabinet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0506145394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1220 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0506145394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The extended council of the opposition Ukrainian 
people's movement, or the Rukh, decided at the session on Sunday 
to form a shadow Cabinet. 
  A shadow government will work out alternative programs for 
the country's development and carry out constructive opposition 
activities towards the present Cabinet, said the movement's 
leader, Vyacheslav Chornovyl in an interview to Interfax-Ukraine. 
  The Rukh council also decided to "denounce even more the 
Communist ideology and carry out a resolute struggle with the 
ruling party which tries to stop the economic reforms". 
  The movement's leadership recommended that primary 
organizations focus efforts on local elections which will take 
place on June 26 alongside the presidential ones. Chornovyl 
believes the Rukh may win the mayors' elections in over 20 large 
cities and try to win the elections in another 700 
constituencies. 
  The council confirmed the intention to vote at the 
presidential elections against former prime minister Leonid 
Kuchma and the current parliament speaker Aleksandr Moroz 
because it believes they pose danger for sovereignty and 
independence of Ukraine. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

