<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Speaker Receives CSCE Commissioner </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Speaker Receives CSCE Commissioner </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306210994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1936 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0306210994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Kiev 3 June TASS -- A meeting of Deputy Ukrainian 
Parliament Speaker Oleg Demin with CSCE High Commissioner for 
Ethnic Minorities Max van der Stoel was held here today. The 
commissioner has arrived in Kiev on a working visit at the 
invitation of the Ukrainian Government. 
  The deputy speaker informed the visitor of the current 
social, economic and political situation in Ukraine, the work of 
the new parliament and the situation in the Crimea, where a 
Ukrainian parliamentary delegation is searching for 
constitutional and law-governed ways to settle the problems. 
  In his turn, Max van der Stoel said he values high the 
Ukrainian policy on ethnic relations, including the provision of 
ethnic minorities rights. In his opinion, this policy is a 
model one. 
  He counts on the Ukrainian and Crimean governments to start 
negotiations and find a way out of the situation. In his 
opinion, there are plenty of ways and one should only wish to 
use them. 
  Max van der Stoel called for larger and more efficient 
assistance to Ukraine in order to help it overcome the economic 
crisis. He stressed he will initiate this and other issues 
within the limits of his competence and abilities. 
  The meeting was friendly and cordial, and proved high 
interest of the sides in development of comprehensive 
cooperation and settlement of all disputable issues in a legal 
way and through compromises which unite people and bring them 
peace and good. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

