<H3> <TI>   CSCE Commissioner on Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CSCE Commissioner on Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0406145694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1435 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0406145694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM correspondent Alexey Trotsenko] </F>
  [Text] Kiev, 4 June (TASS) -- A major principle of CSCE is 
inviolability of borders; this principle should be the basic one 
in the search for mutually acceptable solutions of 
Ukrainian-Crimean problems, CSCE High Commissioner for Ethnic 
Minorities Max Van der Stoel said here today. 
  The high commissioner has been to Ukraine on a four-day 
visit 
to meet Ukrainian and Crimean officials and discuss the 
situation around the Crimea. 
  In his words, CSCE will render comprehensive assistance to 
the settlement of Ukrainian-Crimean problems on the basis of 
inviolability of borders. 

</TEXT>

