<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Baltops-94' Joint Naval Exercises Start 6 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Baltops-94' Joint Naval Exercises Start 6 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306194194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1810 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0306194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] From June 6 through 10 in the southern part of the 
Baltic Sea the Baltops-94 joint exercises will take place. 
Participants include vessels from Russia, the USA, Belgium, 
Denmark, Germany, Finland, Latvia, Lithuania, the Netherlands, 
Norway, Poland, Sweden and Estonia. Russia will be represented 
by the patrol boat Neustrashimy, the press service of the 
Russian navy told Interfax. 
  During the exercises firing and rescue operations will be 
practiced. For the first time the exercises will include U.S. 
parachutists from the Orion naval aircraft making a landing on 
water to be taken aboard by the Russian ship Neustrashimy. 
  During the exercises the ships are due to call in at Kiel 
(Germany) and Gdynia (Poland). 

</TEXT>

