<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   CSCE Secretary General Visits CIS Headquarters </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CSCE Secretary General Visits CIS Headquarters </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606201894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1501 
GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0606201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By BELINFORM correspondent Larisa Klyuchnikova -- TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk, 6 June -- Commonwealth Executive Secretary 
Ivan Korotchenya received CSCE Secretary General Wilhelm 
Hoeynck, who arrived in Minsk at Korotchenya 's invitation on 
Sunday [5 June], at the CIS headquarters today. A productive 
conversation about common CIS and CSCE problems took place. The 
"hot" spots in particular were discussed. 
  Wilhelm Hoeynck noted that in his view the current concept 
of 
peacemaking should be amended slightly. For example, he thinks 
that the concept should reflect the need for the parties in a 
conflict to agree to the introduction of UN forces and to the 
conditions for cooperation between observers and the 
peacekeeping forces; and the procedure for withdrawing troops 
from the conflict zone should be set out. 
  I. Korotchenya and W. Hoeynck were in mutual understanding 
on 
the issue of strengthing links between the CSCE and CIS working 
bodies and joining efforts in peacemaking activities. The CSCE 
secretary general was also interested in the CIS situation, 
prospects, and integrationary policies. Detailed answers were 
given to these questions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

